headline: Streetwise | Is This the Dot-Com Bubble All Over Again?
summary: Back in 1999 the internet was the first, and often the only, topic of conversation with investors.  The parallels of today’s artificial-intelligence boom with the dot-com bubble go much further, but there’s also a very big difference: Stocks went up a lot more back then.
